{{no footnotes|date=August 2017}} '''Cumulative dose''' is the total dose resulting from repeated exposures of [[ionizing radiation]] to an occupationally exposed worker to the same portion of the body, or to the whole body, over a period of time.
In medicine, the total amount of a drug or radiation given to a patient over time; for example, the total dose of radiation given in a series of radiation treatments. ==See also==
